review_blob: Slightly fruity nose with pepper and hay, very herbal. taste is fairly dry, light honey and pear, fresh herbs and flowers. Fishes with a menthol-like szechuan peppercorn note. The peppercorn is obvious, without being obnoxious. Well done.

Super hoppy nose with citrus and herbs, some light honey and a touch of past.  Taste is very dry, moderately bitter, lots of herbs and fresh citrus, somelight juicy sweetness at the end. Fantastic stuff, could drink all day.
Sweet cotton candy and grapefruit nose, lots of sticky hops, resin. Taste is moderately sweet, moderately bitter, lots of grapefruit, pine, apricot and tangerine. Slightly astringent finish.
Big fresh citrus hop nose with light honey. Tate is lightly sweet, moderately bitter, light cotton candy, lots of grapefruit, tangerine, and fresh flowers.
Berry and cola nose with lots of toffee, biscuity malts. Tate is fairly dry, lots of toffee, some dough, raisins. Kinda meh.
Dusty, musty nose with light golden fruit and fresh flowers. Taste is lightly sweet, doughy malts, light honey and pears.

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Light biscuit and toffee with a touch of herbal hops. Flavor is very light and refreshing, light golden raisins, light caramel and honey, lots of fresh herbs and flowers. insanely drinkable.
beer_name: Hair of the Dog Little Dog Light

review_blob: Very funky lactic nose with strong grapefruit and lemon, lots of apricot. Tate is lightly sweet and lightly sour, flavors are a bit dull, light cotton candy, some citrus and golden fruit juice. Soft with gentle carbonation.
Doughy malts with some light citrus and floral notes. Taste us fairly dry and moderately bitter, somewhat medicinal with a bit of aspirin.
Sweet and sugary nose, light funk and acidity. Taste is cotton candy, light fruit, rather bland, moderately sweet, lightly sour, some oxidation. Very disappointing.
Sweet caramel nose with lots of cherry. Fairly sweet, lightly tart, lots of cherry, tons of toffee, dark fruit.
Cola and caramel nose, light oxidation and sherry. Taste is moderately sweet, lightly sour, light cherry, lots of prunes, balsamic vinegar.
beer_name: Dark Horse King Of The Forest

review_blob: Nice fruity nose, lots of sweet citrus, light floral notes and funky cheese. Lightly sweet and tart, light citrus, a touch of honey, dusty treat. Nice.

$16 drain pour. Overwhelming ethyl acetate (nail polish remover, solvent) nasty sweet vinegar mixed with sweaty goat and bile. Could only manage a small sip.  A very disappointing beer that should have been dumped by the brewer. AVOID.
beer_name: Dark Horse Lambeak Wants Blood Orange

review_blob: Very spicy and citrus-y nose. Flavor is dominated by coriander and orange peel, light cotton candy and honey.
Slightly sweet caramel and nut nose. Taste is light to moderately sweet, lightly bitter; light toffee, some dark fruit and nuts. Very drinkable. Solid.
Nice roasty nose with a touch of chocolate and licorice. Taste is fairly dry, lots of coffee and cocoa nibs, light cola and dark fruit. Very nice.
beer_name: Bad Brewing No Stout About It

review_blob: Nice sticky resinous nose, with a touch of cotton candy. Taste is lightly sweetand fairly bitter with lots of sticky hops, pine and citrus, some darkness and light golden fruit. Finishes with sweet honey and pithy bitterness.

Sour fruit nose with sea salt and a touch of stinkfoot. Taste is moderately sour, some acetic acid,  lots of moldy grapefruit, sour cherry and cheese. Finishes with a slightly vegetal rubarb note that is lightly astringent.

2 year old. Tap at Churchkey. Grapefruit and lemon nose, very juicy, light cheese and yogurt. Taste is quite sour, lots of funk and cheese, light acetone sweetness. Acetic acid finish. Body is slightly flabby.
Light bourbon and cola nose with a touch of roasted coffee. Taste is lightly sweet milk chocolate and molasses with light buttery bourbon, just a touch of spicy wood. Very soft texture.
beer_name: Stillwater Barrel Aged Series - Folklore, the tale of Van Winkle

review_blob: Big sweet fruity nose, gobs of berry jam. Taste is moderately sweet, just lightly tart, fairly well balanced and it remains fairly drinkable.  Lots of berry, light caramel cream, some apple juice and light hibiscus. Finish is lightly tannic and bitter. Nicely done.

Cidery, fruity nose with a nice moldy grapefruit rind funk and light vinegar.  Taste is lightly sweet and moderately sour, light acetic acid, but its a tolerable level. Bright citrus fruit, dusty yeast and lots of red fruit. Nice.
Light honey and a touch of citrus hops in the nose. Taste is fairly dru and lightly bitter, with grainy malt, citrus rind and biscuit.
beer_name: Push Brewing Gate Drop Pale Ale

review_blob:
Super fresh pineapple nose with dusty yeast and cotton candy
 Taste is lightly sweet with honey and citrus peel. Light funk, some cobweb. Very nice.
beer_name: Stillwater Now & Then Project - Cellar Door

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Sweet, fruity nose, slightly boozy. Very sweet, raw sugar, candied orange peel, bleh.
Big, oily dark chocolate nose with heavy roasted coffee. Taste is sweet, lots of dark chocolate and coffee. Soft and creamy. Very nice.
Big chocolate and coconut nose, just a little bit green. Taste is sweet and moderately bitter, lots of chocolate and roast, plenty of buttery coconut. Tasty.
Nice floral and citrus hop nose with a touch of honey. Lightly sweet taste with quite a bit of grainy, biscuit malt. Hops are pretty nice, lots of fresh flowers and tangerine.
Sugary toffee and chocolate nose with lots of coffee. Taste is lightly sweet and lightly tart with chocolate, coffee, molasses and cinnamon.
Big sweet nose with lots of pine. Flavor is sweet and fruity with lots of citrus and pine, lots of caramel and honey.
Sulfur nose with some chemical cleaner notes and lots of herbal and floral notes. Cleans up a lot as out breathes. Lightly sweet toffee, tart cherry, light cola and toffee.

Big sweet grape juice nose with lots of dark fruit and toffee, light cola and vinegar. Sweet and sour taste with lots of acetic acid, some dark fruit and cherry, some caramel and light chocolate and molasses.
Sweet and lightly tart nose with some dark fruit, lots of cherry, and light toffee. Taste is lightly sweet, lightly tart, lots of raisins, some caramel and cola, light berry. Decent.
Big funky golden fruit nose, lots of pineapple, some sweetness. Taste is lightly sweet, lightly tart, lightly bitter, lots of floral hops, tons of citrus, funky dirty yeast and honey.
Light citrus and herbal hops aroma, slightly grassy. Taste is lightly sweet, lightly bitter, lots of herbs and floral hops, lightly fruity.
Nice sticky citrus and dank hop nose, very juicy. Taste is lightly sweet, moderately bitter, lots of pine and citrus juice and rind, very tropical, light honey and floral hops.
Sweet and tart nose with cherries and caramel. Taste is light to moderately sweet, lightly sour, with cherry, light vinegar, some raw sugar and cobweb-y yeast.
beer_name: De Proefbrouwerij / Hair of the Dog Flanders Fred

review_blob: Sweet caramel and rye nose with a touch of raisin. Taste is light to moderately sweet, lots of dark fruit, light cola, light chocolate and eye bread. Decent.
Really nice floral nose with some light honey. Taste is rather dry, and just lightly bitter, theres a fair amount of apple juice, and hay and lemon, light herb. Solid.
Coconut and floral nose with a touch of honey. Taste is sweet and a bit hot and boozy, light honey, some lavender, light cotton candy and pears.
Cider and lemon juice nose. Taste is moderately sweet with a light sourness, lots of apple cider vinegar and old stale wine notes, lots of raw sugar.
Nice, crisp, pine and citrus aroma with light doughy malts. The flavor is fairly dry and lightly bitter. The hopping is nice, with plenty of citrus. Malts are a bit dull. Very enjoyable beer overall.
Sweet and sour cherry nose with a bit of cola. Taste is sharp and sour, some cherry and skins, light spice and nut. Not bad.
Sharply sour and buttery nose with a bit of ripe cheese. Taste is moderately sour, and lightly sweet with lots of lemon juice and honeysuckle. Decent.
Dry, dusty nose with a touch of grain and herbal hops. Taste is relatively dry, light crisp malt, some light honey, fresh grassy and herbal hops. Very nice.

Sweet, light honey nose with a touch of apple and leaves. Flavor is lightly sweet, with honey and ripe pear, some raw sugar, light citrus juice, and a touch of dusty yeast. Fairly solid, but could use improved carbonation retention.

Nice grapefruit and funk nose, picking up lots of citrus with some cheese and mold. Taste is just a touch sweet, pleasant level of acidity, lots of cheese funk, some moldy grapefruit rind. A touch of melon sweetness, and dusty yeast. Very soft body with light and gentle carbonation.
Nice schwartz, fairly true to style. Nice dark fruit and toffee nose. Flavor similar, with touch of roast.
Lightly sweet, toffee and dark fruit nose. Lightly sweet taste, lightly bitter with light toffee, some herbs, a hint of golden fruit and raisins. Nicely done.
